description:
Implement `hx-visually-hidden` (T4 Infrastructure) — utility component that hides content visually while keeping it accessible to screen readers.

**Files to create** in `packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-visually-hidden/`:
- `index.ts`, `hx-visually-hidden.ts`, `hx-visually-hidden.styles.ts`, `hx-visually-hidden.stories.ts`, `hx-visually-hidden.test.ts`

**Props:** none

**Slots:** default (the visually-hidden content)

**CSS Parts:** `base`

**Implementation:** Apply the standard visually-hidden CSS pattern:
```css
:host {
  position: absolute !important;
  width: 1px !important;
  height: 1px !important;
  padding: 0 !important;
  margin: -1px !important;
  overflow: hidden !important;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0) !important;
  white-space: nowrap !important;
  border: 0 !important;
}
```

**ARIA:** No ARIA role — the slotted content provides its own semantics. Do NOT use `visibility: hidden` or `display: none` as those hide from screen readers too.

**Quality gates:** type-check zero errors, tests (content accessible, not visually rendered), axe-core zero violations, Storybook demo showing screen reader announcement pattern, bundle < 1KB.

Register in `packages/hx-library/src/index.ts` and `packages/hx-library/vite.config.ts`.

